d as main module\\n\\n#### **src/scheduler.ts** - Job Scheduler Class\\n**Interface**:\\n```typescript\\ninterface JobDefinition {\\n  name: string\\n  handler: () => Promise<void> | void\\n  intervalMs: number\\n  timer?: ReturnType<typeof setInterval>\\n  lastRun?: Date\\n  runCount: number\\n  errors: string[]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Class Methods**:\\n- `register(name, handler, intervalMs)`: Registers a job\\n- `start()`: Starts all jobs on intervals\\n- `stop()`: Stops all jobs\\n- `runOnce(name)`: Executes a job immediately\\n- `getStatus()`: Returns array of {name, lastRun, runCount, errorCount}\\n- `isRunning()`: Returns running state\\n\\n**Features**:\\n- Tracks job execution count and errors\\n- Uses setInterval for scheduling\\n- Async/await support for job handlers\\n- Error collection without throwing\\n\\n#### **src/jobs/sync.ts** - Data Sync Job\\n**Exports**:\\n- `syncJob()`: Main sync job\\n- `syncSingleUser(userId)`: Syncs individual user\\n\\n**Features**:\\n- `fetchExternalUsers()`: Returns hardcoded external users\\n- Syncs external users to local DB if not already present\\n- Skips duplicate emails\\n- Logs sync statistics (synced count, skipped count)\\n- `syncSingleUser()` returns boolean success/failure\\n\\n#### **src/jobs/cleanup.ts** - Maintenance Job\\n**Interface**:\\n```typescript\\ninterface CleanupResult {\\n  staleRecords: number\\n  cleanedUp: number\\n  duration: number\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Exports**:\\n- `cleanupJob()`: Returns CleanupResult\\n- `getCleanupThresholdDays()`: Returns 365 days\\n\\n**Features**:\\n- Identifies users older than 365 days as stale\\n- Simulates cleanup (doesn't actually delete)\\n- Measures execution duration in milliseconds\\n- Logs cleanup statistics\\n\\n#### **tests/scheduler.test.ts**\\nTests for scheduler (6 test cases):\\n- Registers a job\\n- Runs job once\\n- Tracks run count\\n- Throws for unknown job\\n- Starts and stops\\n\\n#### **tests/sync.test.ts**\\nTests for sync job (4 test cases):\\n- Syncs e